CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 3, 1957, pg. A2 reads: "NAACP Drive Ends - Mrs . Marion B. Jordon, executive secretary of the Pittsburgh NAACP branch, addresses some of the industrious workers who helped to make the 1957 membership campaign a success. The meeting was held at Wesley Center AME Zion Church recently. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Marion Bond Jordon addressing group in Wesley Center AME Zion Church during end of NAACP membership campaign
